to the editor as the experience of sharing a bedroom with a brother or sister becomes less common for young people growing up in our affluent society colleges offer students an advantage by insisting that double rooms remain part of the campus residential experience for a price colleges offer students privacy front page jan 27 the experience of having had a roommate helps build a collaborative and cooperative spirit it is not a privilege to be deprived of community and why create a false hierarchy among students based on wealth for these reasons when barnard embarked on the renovation of its residence halls we started with the assumption that all first year students would have roommates and that only seniors would be guaranteed a single room this strategy helps students achieve something more cherished than privacy lifelong friendships dorothy denburg dean barnard college new york jan 28 2003

